flowRoot.flowPara: To have the key signed, the other person must enter the security code, or scan the QR code.
Select a key to present for signing.
To sign someone's key, scan their QR or security code.
To sign the key, confirm that you want to sign the following key. This will generate an email that must be sent in order to complete the signing process.
List shows your keys, including their UIDs, times signed, and expiry date.
Camera combobox is only shown when there is more than one camera.
Dialog pops up when a valid QR code or securitycode is detected. A sound should alert the user that this has happened.
Errors are displayed in a message dialog.
To sign someone's key, enter their security code, or plug in a web cam to scan their QR code.
If there isn't a camera, don't show the feed (and suggest that the user plugs one in).
Clicking a list row opens a dialog window with the security and QR code.
To have the key signed, the other person must enter the security code, or scan the QR code.
